oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Tickets of the Memphi
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Mystic Memphi; secret societies;
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: A ticket to the Palace of the Exposition in 1879; A ticket to the New Memphis Theatre Feb. 14, 1874, hosted by the Memphi; A Tableux for Return of the Memphi from Egypt and the Banquet of The Deities on Mount Olympus. White Palace of the Exposition ticket, hexagonal 7 x 3.75 in. mounted on poster board; Purple New Memphis Theatre Ticket 4.5 x 2.5 in. mounted on poster board; White tableaux quadrilateral shaped 4 x 5.75 in mounted on poster board.
oai_dc:dc.dc:contributor: Manuscript collection processed by John Jones
